HEADWORD: Scalpel
<hw>Scal"pel</hw> <pr>(sk⟦acr⟧l"p⟦ecr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scalpellum</ets>, dim. of <ets>scalprum</ets> a knife, akin to
<ets>scalpere</ets> to cut, carve, scrape: cf. F.
<ets>scalpel</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>A small knife with a
